==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wirþa-'' ‘turn, become’, from Indo-European ''*wert-'' ‘turn’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[wertha]], Old Saxon [[werþan]] (Dutch [[worden]]), Old High German [[werdan]] (German [[werden]]), Old Norse [[verða]] (Swedish [[varda]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌰𐌹𐍂𐌸𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root is also the source of Avestan ''varət-'', Latin [[vertere]], Baltic ''*wert-'' (Lithuanian [[versti|ver̃sti]]), Slavic ''*vrьteti-'' (Russian [[вертеть]]).

